Create a collection from a list of datasets

Collections of datasets are permanent, ordered lists of datasets that can be passed to tools and workflows in order to have analyses done on each member of the entire group. This interface allows you to create a collection and re-order the final collection.

  • Rename elements in the list by clicking on the existing name .
  • Discard elements from the final created list by clicking on the Discard button.
  • Reorder the list by clicking and dragging elements. Select multiple elements by clicking on them and you can then move those selected by dragging the entire group. Deselect them by clicking them again or by clicking the Clear selected link.
  • Click to begin again as if you had just opened the interface.
  • Click to sort datasets alphabetically.
  • Click the Cancel button to exit the interface.

Once your collection is complete, enter a name and click Create list .
